<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 03 at 7:05PM CDT until May 06 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 PM CDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL POTTER AND SOUTHWESTERN MOORE COUNTIES...
At 705 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Masterson, or
15 miles south of Dumas, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Masterson and Four Way.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
